                  <div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td class="alt2" style="border:1px inset">
			
				<div>Originally Posted by <strong>jhorry</strong></div>
				<div style="font-style:italic">Sorry for my rude reply earlier, i was having a stressful day <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Smilie" class="inlineimg" /><br />
<br />
<br />
I can see where many of you are comming from in not wanting to loose the sorcerer's flavor, and also please understand that when i did the numbers on these abilities, i didnt match them up with the current in game numbers.<br />
<br />
<br />
I basically took my version of Taqmir's and used it as my &quot;base&quot; to build the other values.<br />
<br />
Upon looking, it appears that Taqmir's at level 50 is around 1000 base damage with a 3.5 second cast, is this correct?<br />
<br />
If so, basically HALF all of the numbers you see, and that would be much closer to the in game numbers.<br />
<br />
<br />
For instance, my Flame Spear's damage would really be about 6,000, half of the current big finisher.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
I would love to hear some thoughts about improving the functionality of choas volley though.<br />
<br />
<br />
Would you guys like the spell better if:<br />
<br />
Instead of spaming it to ramp it up, it would be an instant cast with a reuse timer, and would take fewer casts to get the same effect, allowing the use of other spells inbetween these reuse timers?<br />
<br />
Example:<br />
<br />
Instead of 14 casts to each the max effect, make it 4 casts, in that same 28 second time period it takes for the spell to ramp up if you had chain cast the current one.<br />
<br />
This would be: Instant cast, 7 second recast, leaving a 5 second window inbetween each cast of Chaos Volly to use other nukes.<br />
<br />
Using other nukes would not reset CV, so the option to gain higher dps at a lower damage to energy ratio is an option, though exclusively using CV would be one of the most efficient ways to dps (just as it currently is)<br />
<br />
<br />
So, instead of ramping up a little bit with each cast, it would ramp up a lot with each cast, but they would be spaced out more, allowing you to use other spells along side CV.<br />
<br />
<br />
That would up sorcerer's dps enough to match rangers on this longer fights i think.<br />
<br />
<br />
What do you guys think?<br />
<br />
<br />
It would be like:<br />
<br />
Instant low damage CV, 2 sec global, 5 seconds to cast your nukes of choice, instant medium damage CV, 2 second global, 5 seconds to nuke, heavy CV, 2 sec global, 5 sec cast, MASSIVE CV, 2 sec global, 5 sec cast.<br />
<br />
Then CV resets after the final cast.<br />
<br />
So any fight that is going to last long enough for CV to reach its 4th cast, it would be worth using, but if the fight is shorter, you might be better off using Char and the like.<br />
<br />
CV would be doing exactly the same damage it currently does, but instead of 14 casts it would be condensed into 4 casts with space inbetween, allowing for more damage opportunities, cc, rooting and what have you in the 5 seconds of avalible casting time inbetween each CV.<br />
<br />
<br />
Thoughts?</div>
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div>
