		<div id="post_message_1169881">
                  
                  SDF is 498,  Int is 24%, SDR is 39,  Critic is 916<br />
<br />
I chose to go for &quot;pure critic&quot; based on the idea that a few Critic on CV after the 10th cast will give<br />
much higher return than all other stats.<br />
The idea was that if i can get Critic around 40% i reach &quot;critical mass&quot;.<br />
Also if i remember well Cylus said the &quot;base critic&quot; is 50% Bonus.<br />
<br />
The side-effect is that CV now becomes my main nuke.<br />
Because a critic with CV (even at 1st cast) means i get a 3-5k finisher.<br />
Which is still better than what you can hope with &quot;normal&quot; spells.<br />
<br />
Also the mana usage is very low, since CV spam = feedback and if i critic on a CV<br />
i get a 2 second feedback, from the GCD due to the finisher.<br />
<br />
Usually i nuke with something like<br />
<br />
CV1-1200  CV2-2200(Critic) 3000 (Finisher) CV3-1900 CV3-3000(Critic) 4500(FinisherCritic) etc etc.<br />
<br />
I'm very happy with the results, the DPS is quite good, and the mana use is very low (great if you downrank).<br />
<br />
But i didnt feel like nuking at 38.2% Critic rate when in group.<br />
<br />
I still have to finish RI Helm/ToT Neck (for more %Critic).<br />
<br />
<a href="http://vgplayers.station.sony.com/characters.vm?characterId=77309413874" target="_blank">http://vgplayers.station.sony.com/ch...Id=77309413874</a>
                  
		</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
