				<div>   </div>
			</div>				
	
	
	
	</td>
	
	<td class="alt1" id="td_post_1170023">
	
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_1170023">
                  
                  <div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td class="alt2" style="border:1px inset">
			
				<div>Originally Posted by <strong>Sasami</strong></div>
				<div style="font-style:italic">I think all your suggestions are a nerf or for CV. I don&#8217;t know why you insist on reuse timer, there is no benefit on reuse timer. dps calculation is done on cast time not on reuse time if you increase damage per cast time you move balance.<br />
<br />
If I had to choose, I would take the version which is currently in game.<br />
<br />
Are you sure you like to play a Sorcerer, the big nukes on long recasts are the design of the Druid. Maybe trying out a Druid will give you what you are looking for?<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
If you look at the feedback from some high lvl Sorcerer there is nothing to catch up. We may be there already.</div>
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div>
<br />
1.) Please respect others, telling someone &quot;this might not be the class for you&quot; can be taken as an insult, even if it is not intended as such.<br />
<br />
2.) You are exagerating the scope of the situation. <br />
<br />
We are only talking about a 7 second recast, and you will do the exact same dps with CV as you currently do, but in less casts.<br />
<br />
If you could, please list how your CV scales, what the cap is, and how many casts it takes to reach the cap.<br />
<br />
The reason this 7 second recast improves your dps is it lets you deal exactly the same dps with CV while being able to use nukes inbetween, instead of chain casting CV you Cast, have 5 seconds after the GCD before CV is ready to use again, then CV will hit for all the damage that you would have done during the reuse timer had you been spaming the current version.<br />
<br />
So, you could toss a flame spear or a taqmir's or a char or any other nuke during this 5 second window, + the current damage of CV.<br />
<br />
<br />
So, lets just say with CV you could cast it 4 times in 7 seconds, going 1200, 1400, 1600, 1800 or how ever it actually scales.<br />
<br />
With my version your first cast would be 1200, 2 sec GCD, 5 seconds to cast what ever you want, then the next CV at 7 seconds would land for 4600.<br />
<br />
It would be the same total damage, but you would spend less time casting it.<br />
<br />
It would still function as a &quot;rev up&quot; nuke that gets better the longer the fight lasts.<br />
<br />
It would take 6 casts in 28 seconds to max it. <br />
<br />
(14 X 2 sec GCD = 28 seconds to max the current CV unless they changed the mechanics of the spell since i played with it, correct?)<br />
<br />
Think of it like this:<br />
<br />
In 28 seconds, you might deal i dont know, 20k damage, with either spell.<br />
<br />
Now, which sounds better:<br />
<br />
20K damage from spaming one spell continually over the 28 seconds<br />
<br />
or<br />
<br />
20k damage from casting a spell 6 times over the 28 seconds, leaving 18 seconds worth of free casting time to use your other nukes.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
Even if they did have to tone down CV's damage just a tad, the potiential to get in more casts would likely increase your dps even higher than it currently is, while alowing more flexability than &quot;spam CV&quot; to get the best effect.<br />
<br />
I know CV is currently effective.<br />
<br />
It takes very little energy and health to deal massive amounts of damage, but honestly, even if you were slamming down 100,000 damage nukes with it, is it fun to just use one nuke?<br />
<br />
I personally have never seen a game where spaming 1 nuke is the &quot;best&quot; way to make something dead.<br />
(well i take that back... Ultima spell on Final Fantasy games usually does the trick hehe <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Smilie" class="inlineimg" /> )<br />
<br />
To me that is so one demensional that you might as well set up a macro program to auto adjust your range and press CV constantly.<br />
<br />
<br />
So, my opinion on CV is its a spell that is infact functional, VERY functional indeed, but it completely kills the enjoyment, and more importantly, any sense of strategy with the class if you end up just spaming it w/o being able to use other abilities.<br />
<br />
I really hope the devs can find a way to make it a very <b>important </b>nuke for sorcerers without being &quot;the one nuke to rule them all.&quot;<br />
<br />
The only way i could see to do that is:<br />
<br />
A) weaken it so that it is an efficient nuke but not our best dps ability.<br />
<br />
B) strengthen our other nukes so they are more dps than CV spam but at a higher energy cost.<br />
<br />
C) Add a recast timer inbetween each ramp up, make each ramp up MUCH higher, which allows us to use other nukes inbetween.<br />
<br />
<br />
Anyone else have any suggestions?<br />
<br />
<br />
I think the original intent of CV was to be a dangerous spell that can do great damage after it has ramped up, but now it is not nearly dangerous enough in most situation to warrent using other spells, and our other spells are so much less effective that it hurts you dps to use them instead of CV.<br />
<br />
<br />
To me it is a self-defeating cycle currently:<br />
<br />
Use CV all the time (provided the fight lasts long enough) which takes no strategy beyond &quot;dont kill yourself with it&quot;, or use other spells that are less effective. <br />
<br />
I just cant see where CV would not be the best choice (baring AOE fights), unless risk of losing health is high.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
I'm in no way trying to make the sorcerer class suck, but rather im trying to find a solution to a perplexing problem:<br />
<br />
<br />
How do you make Chaos Volley a good and useful spell with senerioes it is useful in without making it the be-all-end-all spell for all senerioes?<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
In its current form, it just feels like a &quot;cool concept&quot; ability that made all other nukes obsolete, which to me is a bad thing, but i can respect those who find pressing one nuke for the rest of their sorcerer's playtime<br />
(although i cannot comprehend how it is fun personally, but fun is subjective)<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
So, play arm chair dev for a bit guys, and try to find some ways to make Chaos Volley a &quot;good&quot; spell but not the &quot;best&quot; spell.
                  
		</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
