	<td class="alt1" id="td_post_1170124">
	
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_1170124">
                  
                  I think I figured out the ranger's higher parse, are you accouting for windsong's broken parsing? It displays its TOTAL damage with each hit, so it might show it hitting for 5000 on 5 hits, when it really hit for 1000 on 5 hits.<br />
<br />
So in reality, not counting the ranger's numbers, who was the next closest?<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
Btw, if anyone could reply with the actual damage, listed damage, energy costs, casting time, reuse time, and number of ranks that their spells have, that would be great <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Smilie" class="inlineimg" /><br />
<br />
Oh, and your intell, wisdom, crit, energy bar and health bar amounts, and stuff like that would be wonderful to, especially level 50 sorcerers as thats where im trying to balance the skills to.<br />
<br />
<br />
<div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td class="alt2" style="border:1px inset">
			
				<div>Originally Posted by <strong>EmiliaSEB</strong></div>
				<div style="font-style:italic">CV is perfect, do not touch that spell.<br />
<br />
The spells that need a big boost are &quot;non CV&quot; ones.<br />
Because their DPS under all conditions really really crappy.<br />
<br />
As i showed in another thread with 25+25 Spell Haste...<br />
<a href="http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?t=50285&amp;page=2" target="_blank">http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthr...t=50285&amp;page=2</a><br />
CV needs 7 cast to do more DPS than chain Seradons<br />
CV needs 9 cast to do more DPS than chain FS at max range.<br />
<br />
This doesnt look bad, but 25% worn spell haste is enormous.<br />
I dont expect anyone to go over 12-15% specially sorcerers who's MAIN spell is instant.<br />
<br />
What we need is a small reduction of casting time on &quot;non instant&quot; spells.<br />
And a HUGE mana reduction, because chain FS costs almost 2 times more mana than chain CV.<br />
<br />
Tweak our spells. dont remake them.</div>
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div>
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
I did tweak Chaos Volley. Exactly the same damage, just in fewer casts and with room inbetween these casts to use other abilities.<br />
<br />
<br />
I also suggested that the other abilities could be vastly improved, but here is the deal with that:<br />
<br />
<br />
We could tweak every nuke up in damage, to make them comparable to CV, and we could lower the energy cost.<br />
<br />
But, if we do that, we change a core conept of the class, being that fire spells are &quot;higher in dps but costly for energy.&quot; If we reduce their energy cost too much then they become the main cannon fodder.<br />
<br />
Arcane was intended to be our primary source of damage, as in the bulk of our dps was to be arcane based nukes. These return energy if spaced out,, cost health, or cost endurance in order to have very high damage per energy used, so they are basically our dots, as they are how we go for lower dps but lasting longer with our energy.<br />
<br />
Fire based nukes were supposed to be our flashy big hits and heavy spike dps, but be horrible for long term dps if we are concerned with energy. Need to burn something down? Pull out the fire nukes.<br />
<br />
Ice based nukes were supposed to be our quick, hinderance nukes, intended to keep a foe away from us inorder to use the above two nuke schools. Im also they include agro reduction into our ice nukes, as it fits the theme. I dont think they were ever intended to be a viable way to deal damage, but they give us the time and space to deal damage.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
Now, thinking with those basic concepts, here was what i conceptualized in my mind. Im basing this off of a sorcerer having around 6000 energy to use, though i would like to see the numbers for your energy pools if you guys dont mind sharing:<br />
<br />
<br />
Flame<br />
<br />
I would assume that Flame Spear and Char and Falling Star should be our best dps when spammed, but run us DRY on energy in a short time.<br />
<br />
Falling Star = 2.0 sec cast, 1500 damage, 375 energy, 4 d/e, 750 dps.<br />
<br />
Char = instant cast, 6 sec recast, and would deal 3000 damage, 800 energy, 3.75 d/e, 500 dps.<br />
<br />
Flame Spear = 2.0 cast, 18 sec reuse, 6000 damage for 1300 energy, 4.5d/e<br />
<br />
<br />
So, if you wished, you could do Flame Spear &gt; Char &gt; 2 Falling &gt; char &gt; 2 falling &gt; char &gt; 2 falling &gt; repeates with FS, this would be maximum burn dps.<br />
<br />
That one chain would yield:<br />
<br />
Damage: 24,000<br />
DPS: 1200 over 20 seconds.<br />
Cost: 5950 energy (99% of the energy bar)<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
Arcane<br />
<br />
I would assume that Taqmir's, Shocking grasp, and Chaos Volley should be our efficient dps. Only Taq would have the returning energy, the others would be calculated in with their cost, and would not interfere with Taq's energy return.<br />
<br />
Taqmir's = 2 sec cast, 1250 damage, returns 30% energy within 6 seconds, 250 energy, 175 energy after the return. 5 d/e before return, 7 d/e after.<br />
<br />
Shocking = instant cast, no recast, and would deal about 1500, 40 end, 150 energy.<br />
<br />
Chaos Volley = instant cast, 4 sec recast, reving up to do 15,000 damage over 28 seconds, 200 energy, 200 health, 7 casts. <br />
<br />
CV1, Shocking, CV2, Shocking, CV3, Taqmir's and 2 sec wait, CV4, Taqmir's and 2 sec wait, CV5, Shocking, CV6, Taqmir's, CV7.<br />
<br />
<br />
Damage: 23,250<br />
DPS: 680 over 34 seconds.<br />
Cost: 2375 energy (40% of the energy bar), 1400 health, 120 endurance<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
With numbers like these, it means you can go all out dps with the flame spells and do 24,000 in 20 seconds and use your energy bar, or you could on that same bar of energy produce 58,125 damage over the course of a minute and 24 seconds or so, or you could mix and match fire and arcane spells to find a middle ground, especially since you have a 10 second window between each CV if you wish before it restarts.<br />
<br />
<br />
That would be the kind of flexability i would like for the sorcerer class, to be able to keep up with a necro / druid /psionicist over time, and vastly demolish them when it comes to burst damage potiential.<br />
<br />
When you add in regen, intell and wisdom buffs, a healer healing, and other raid commadities, the sorcerer will be able to use a lot of their burst damage spells since efficiency is much less of a concern, meaning the sorcerer will likely easily top the parse in the caster archetype, and likely the whole game.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
That would be my &quot;vision&quot; of the sorcerer if they were to stick with the &quot;fire = recklace and inefficient dps&quot; and &quot;arcane = efficient, mainstream dps.&quot;<br />
<br />
<br />
If a group / raid fight is going to last 3 minutes or less, and we have the proper buffs, learning towards flame nukes would be good. If the fight is a logner fight, leaning towards energy nukes a bit more would probably help us maintain the energy.<br />
<br />
Knowing when to burn and when to stride is important for any class, and i think it should be important to us as well.<br />
<br />
<br />
A good example of this is the disciple. They can heal indefinately with their melee arts, but there are times when they need the heavy spike healing of their real heals. Knowing when to stride and when to spike is crucial, along with several other aspects that we dont need to go into with disciples hehe.<br />
<br />
Same is even true for tanks. A Warrior needs to know when to save his big hits or rescues to regain agro, and when to just do his normal hate gain gambit.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
With chaos volley, we seem in a permanent, albiet very good paced stride mode.<br />
<br />
If they boost up the spike damage potiential of our heat nukes, then we will have our needed Burst damage.<br />
<br />
<br />
Btw, is Incinerate, the heavy heat nuke finisher, only triggered from heat nukes, or can chaos volley trigger it? Because i really hope they didnt abandom the trigger concept of only triggering a finisher off the same element, such as only Mimic offof arcane crits, and Incinerate off of fire hits ect, that is a good system.
                  
		</div>
