<br />
Ah i see where this comes into play then, and how that reuse time could then be a real issue.<br />
<br />
On the other hand, if they keep CV dealing great damage or even improve it, and with fewer casts as i described, it could be thought of as a chancey spell. The more classes you have debuffing the foe's resistance, the less chance for this spell to get a resist and not reach its full potiential.<br />
<br />
Most games i have played with a &quot;rev up&quot; spell have this kind of counter mechanic to prevent it from being the best spell / attack in the game. It *can* rev up to be the best dps ability in your arsinal, but it also has the side effect of being reset by a resist.<br />
<br />
Its kind of like hitting a ball back and forth, it picks up moment as you continue to hit it harder, but if one of you misses(a resist), then the process has to start over.<br />
<br />
To me that would make sense with the way the spell sounds, and they could use this chanch to reset as grounds for actually improving its current damage, since you are not garentied to &quot;reach&quot; that final cast. <br />
<br />
Of course, ina raid setting unless the mob is spell resistant, your chances of landing it are vastly improved, making it an ideal, reliable spell for non-resistant, high health mobs, which would be the majority of the contient.<br />
<br />
If they added a much greater chance for Taqmir's to not be resisted, then it would be ideal for resistant mobs, or mobs that through up spell shields, which would be in the minority of the contient probably.<br />
<br />
