		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_1170218">
                  
                  also jhorry the way mimic is coded to work, it needs to have the (energy)feedback in order to know which base damage ability to base itself off of.<br />
<br />
thats why all arcane spells provide feedback, so that when we crit and go to use mimic the game knows what our previous spell cast was.  This is also why we cant use mimic with any of the other nukes.<br />
<br />
so if you remove the arcane feedback from CV you remove its ability to utilize mimic, so I think that definately has to stay there for now.<br />
<br />
The other consideration with giving CV a re-use time, is psi's.  They currently have a lesser version of CV &quot;thought pulse&quot; which deals a greater amount of damage to them (about 30% more than we take) with a 4second re-use timer on it.<br />
<br />
I know already that giving sorc a longer re-cast on cv without modifiying the psi one, will cause a lot of miffed sorc's when the psi gets thought pulse up higher than cv because they have 1 more chance to ramp up the damage over a sorc.<br />
<br />
Currently we have 4 chances if we get a resist spamming CV to continue to ramp up the damage. or it gets reset.  I dont think many of us like the idea of having the restriction of the re-cast timer on CV.<br />
<br />
The way CV currently is set up with the 10sec window, nothing's stopping you from casting other spells during cv's feedback cycle (taq's or FS or finishers) and then hitting cv again before the timer runs out.<br />
<br />
I see CV okay in its current itteration, once falling star and taq's are brought up to par.<br />
<br />
At that point we'll be able to do cv &gt; taq's &gt; FS &gt; cv &gt; taq &gt; FS &gt; and at any time we crit utilize our fire finishers and our cold finishers, while we slowly ramp up cv's damage, in otherwords if you wanted to you have the *choice* (this is the important thing) to cast cv once every 10s and cap it at the 140th second, or spam it every 2 seconds and cap it in 28.
                  
		</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
<tr>
	<td class="alt2">
		<img class="inlineimg" src="images/legacy_images/statusicon/user_offline.gif" alt="Illusive is offline" border="0" />


		
		
		
