		<div id="post_message_1170220">
                  
                  <div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td class="alt2" style="border:1px inset">
			
				<div>Originally Posted by <strong>jhorry</strong></div>
				<div style="font-style:italic">Oh, i just had an interesting idea for an ice spell:<br />
<br />
Frost Snap:<br />
<br />
A fridged blast of wind assults your foe, dealing damage and numbing them. The foe will be less aware to any damage you deal for the next 10 seconds.<br />
<br />
Pros:<br />
<br />
1.) Deals same damage as Cv's first rank.<br />
2.) lowers incoming hate gain on target from sorcerer by 40% for 10 seconds.<br />
3.) instant cast, no recast<br />
4.) low energy cost<br />
<br />
Cons:<br />
<br />
1.) short range, 15m<br />
2.) slows down your dps, though not as much as forget.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
This would be an interesting way of helping with agro, if we cast this before a final CV or a large FS that we focus with an amplification, this 40% could go a long way toward helping us survive the fight <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Smilie" class="inlineimg" /><br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
Also, regarding the quicksilver ring, i thinki have a much better idea that fits with the class as well as helps us function better:<br />
<br />
Instead of a casting speed and reuse speed haste, it would keep its movment boost, and allow us to move quicker while casting a spelll.<br />
<br />
Might cut the casting speed walk's reduction to 1/2 of what it currently is, allowing us to get our max range on Flame Spear and our min range on Frost Snap quicker.</div>
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div>
<br />
an ability like this seems to fit more on our amplify line of spells.  As they are currently the only ones we have with no global cooldown.<br />
<br />
See the way global cooldown works, is even if its instant cast, it still suffers from the 2 sec global cooldown, just like forget does.  when casting a spell the global cooldown starts when you start casting, so even casting forget at 1 sec cast we still have to wait 1 sec before the global cooldown is over.<br />
<br />
in otherwords both abilites would be bound by the 2s global cooldown.  <br />
<br />
So the only way to avoid that is to make the ability not trigger the global cooldown and that fits into the amplify line of abilities.  the short duration instant cast hate reduction for the next 10s seems to fit there the best.<br />
<br />
It would need to be on possibly a 1 min cooldown so we could utilize it once per fight.
                  
		</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
